line=8 fonts=F1-10.9,F2-10.9 bbox=93.84,531.48,503.76,542.39             :     In this study, we define unbounded dependency as a characteristic property of Korean tough
line=9 fonts=F2-10.9 iscore=0.29 bbox=93.84,517.98,503.81,528.89         :     constructions and examine nonlocal Slash feature percolation of Pollard and Sag (1994) cap-
line=10 fonts=F2-10.9 iscore=0.23 bbox=93.84,504.42,503.74,515.33        :     tures the long-distance argument dependency in them. We further show that strong crossover
line=11 fonts=F1-10.9,F2-10.9 iscore=0.15 bbox=93.84,490.86,503.81,501.77:     phenomena  and  coordination facts support a trace analysis of tough constructions. Korean
line=12 fonts=F1-10.9,F2-10.9 iscore=0.23 bbox=93.84,477.3,503.81,488.21 :     tough constructions can be divided into two classes according to different argument realiza-
line=13 fonts=F2-10.9 iscore=0.31 bbox=93.84,463.74,503.77,474.65        :     tion, and our lexical analys accounts for the argument realization of two types of Korean TCs
line=14 fonts=F2-10.9 iscore=0.06 bbox=93.84,450.18,255.69,461.09        :     by using different lexical constraints.

