line=41 fonts=F1-10.9,F2-10.9 bbox=82.92,654.96,525.58,665.87           :  In (2) and (3), we find that nominative marked ka-NPs (or NPs marked with ka’s phonological variant i
line=42 fonts=F2-10.9 iscore=0.17 bbox=72.0,641.4,525.51,652.31         :refer to the same entities as the missing elements in the object position of the embedded predicates. Given
line=43 fonts=F1-10.9,F2-10.9 iscore=0.11 bbox=72.0,627.84,525.58,638.75:that object NPs of the embedded predicates cannot be assigned nominative case in situ, we know that
line=44 fonts=F2-10.9 iscore=0.06 bbox=72.0,614.28,525.59,625.19        :they must appear outside of the embedded clauses in the given examples. The second phrases that takes
line=45 fonts=F1-10.9,F2-10.9 iscore=0.24 bbox=72.0,600.72,525.61,611.63:ki correspond to English gerunds. In these phrases, ki has been treated as a nominalizing affix, which
line=46 fonts=F2-10.9 iscore=0.18 bbox=72.0,587.22,525.53,598.13        :combines with a predicate and maintains the same VALENCE  feature of the predicate while allows the
line=47 fonts=F2-10.9 iscore=0.06 bbox=72.0,573.66,342.39,584.57        :whole phrase to combine with a case marker like normal NPs.
line=48 fonts=F1-10.9,F2-10.9 iscore=0.06 bbox=82.92,560.1,525.55,571.01:  There are two kinds of Korean tough constructions (hereafter TCs), and they can be categorized ac-
line=49 fonts=F2-10.9 iscore=0.30 bbox=72.0,546.54,525.61,557.45        :cording to the case marker on the second nominalized argument. As we see in (2) and (3), one kind takes
line=50 fonts=F2-10.9 iscore=0.15 bbox=72.0,532.98,525.57,543.89        :the case marker ‘ey’ and the other takes the nominative case marker ‘ka’ or ‘i’. We distinguish them
line=51 fonts=F1-10.9,F2-10.9 iscore=0.26 bbox=72.0,519.48,525.6,530.39 :as ki-ey TCs and ki-ka TCs. Both ki-ey and ki-ka TCs show the same kind of long distance dependency
line=52 fonts=F2-10.9 iscore=0.16 bbox=72.0,505.92,525.52,516.83        :as in English TCs, although they show different syntactic behaviors. Their different properties will be
line=53 fonts=F2-10.9 iscore=0.07 bbox=72.0,492.36,237.09,503.27        :discussed in detail in the next section.
line=54 fonts=F2-10.9 iscore=0.06 bbox=82.92,478.8,525.64,489.71        :  In this study, we will investigate basic properties of Korean TCs and provide a theoretical analysis to
line=55 fonts=F2-10.9 iscore=0.06 bbox=72.0,465.24,525.55,476.15        :explain argument realization in TCs. Following Pollard and Sag (1994) who took English TCs to be a
line=56 fonts=F2-10.9 iscore=0.12 bbox=72.0,451.68,525.6,462.59         :sort of weak unbounded dependency construction (UDC), and captured the semantic connectivity in the
line=57 fonts=F1-10.9,F2-10.9 iscore=0.22 bbox=72.0,438.18,510.31,449.09:lexical entry of tough predicates, we argue that the same kind of analysis can be adopted for Korean.
line=58 fonts=F2-10.9 iscore=0.33 bbox=82.92,424.62,525.52,435.53       :  The  organization of this paper is as follows: In section 2, we discuss basic properties of Korean TCs
line=59 fonts=F2-10.9 iscore=0.11 bbox=72.0,411.06,525.59,421.97        :and distinguish them from English. Section 3 deals with unbounded dependency  and the status of a
line=60 fonts=F2-10.9 iscore=0.25 bbox=72.0,397.5,525.73,408.41         :missing element in Korean TCs. As Chae  (1998) noted, an unbounded dependency is a characterizing
line=61 fonts=F2-10.9 iscore=0.24 bbox=72.0,383.94,525.55,394.85        :property of Korean TCs. We claim that a missing element in a TC has the status of a trace and oppose
line=62 fonts=F1-10.9,F2-10.9 iscore=0.14 bbox=72.0,370.44,525.69,381.35:a null pronominal (or pro) analysis. This is supported by semantic and syntactic evidence including
line=63 fonts=F2-10.9 iscore=0.19 bbox=72.0,356.88,525.55,367.79        :crossover and coordination phenomena. In section 4, we show that the connectivity of arguments can be
line=64 fonts=F1-10.9,F2-10.9 iscore=0.18 bbox=72.0,343.32,525.6,354.23 :encoded in the lexical entries of tough predicates. Our lexical analysis provides a natural account for the
line=65 fonts=F2-10.9 iscore=0.06 bbox=72.0,329.76,397.95,340.67        :formation of TCs by correctly capturing unbounded dependencies in them.

