line=170 fonts=F2-10.9 iscore=0.00 bbox=82.92,600.24,525.76,611.15       :  Whether  or not a missing element or a gap is required for the formation of Korean TCs is controversial.
line=171 fonts=F2-10.9 iscore=0.25 bbox=72.0,586.68,525.61,597.59        :Chae (1998) argues that a gap is not required in the complement S or VP in Korean. To support this,
line=172 fonts=F2-10.9 iscore=0.15 bbox=72.0,573.12,525.56,584.03        :he provides two arguments. First, the object position of the embedded predicate can be occupied by an
line=173 fonts=F1-10.9,F2-10.9 iscore=0.06 bbox=72.0,559.56,277.73,570.47:element with phonetic content, as in ki-ka TCs.

