line=211 fonts=F2-10.9 bbox=82.92,606.24,525.59,617.15                          :  We  can find that the same unbounded dependency hold between the first NP and aresumptive pronoun
line=212 fonts=F2-10.9 iscore=0.18 bbox=72.0,592.68,525.72,603.59               :in (17). Thus, we analyze the pronouns in (17) as resumptive pronouns, which can appear in relative
line=213 fonts=F2-10.9 iscore=0.06 bbox=72.0,579.12,210.4,590.03                :clauses and topic constructions.
line=214 fonts=F2-10.9 iscore=0.06 bbox=82.92,565.56,525.52,576.47              :  If we assume  that gaps are normal pronouns, as in Sells (1984) and Chae (1998), the problem of
line=215 fonts=F2-10.9 iscore=0.11 bbox=72.0,552.06,525.63,562.97               :semantic connectivity is simply attributed to binding theory. In contrast, necessary connectivity between
line=216 fonts=F1-10.9,F2-10.9 iscore=0.15 bbox=72.0,538.5,525.6,549.41         :the head noun and a missing element is hard to explain under the analysis of a pro whose antecedent can
line=217 fonts=F2-10.9 iscore=0.10 bbox=72.0,524.94,525.58,535.85               :be found in the context. Thus, we assume that a resumptive pronoun in Korean TCs is another form of
line=218 fonts=F1-10.9,F2-10.9,F2-8.0 iscore=0.05 bbox=72.0,511.38,525.69,523.31:a trace following Vaillette (2001) and Georgopoulos (1991).^{3} This allows us to treat tough constructions
line=219 fonts=F2-10.9 iscore=0.13 bbox=72.0,497.82,525.6,508.73                :as unbounded dependency  constructions (UDCs). A resumptive pronoun that is coindexed with the TC
line=220 fonts=F2-10.9,F2-8.0 iscore=0.14 bbox=72.0,484.32,418.7,496.19         :subject can be represented in HPSG via the propagation of a non-local feature.^{4}
line=221 fonts=F2-10.9 iscore=0.12 bbox=82.92,470.76,525.68,481.67              :  A  resumptive pronoun generally occurs in a sentence with a deeply embedded clause, but in Korean
line=222 fonts=F2-10.9 iscore=0.32 bbox=72.0,457.2,525.66,468.11                :there are rare cases of it occurring in a simple sentence that does not have any embedded clauses. In
line=223 fonts=F2-10.9 iscore=0.21 bbox=72.0,443.64,525.64,454.55               :English, gaps and resumptive pronouns are in near complementary distribution in that the latter appears
line=224 fonts=F2-10.9 iscore=0.07 bbox=72.0,430.08,525.64,440.99               :in islands, whereas the former cannot. In contrast, gaps and resumptive pronouns have overlapping
line=225 fonts=F2-10.9 iscore=0.31 bbox=72.0,416.52,525.61,427.43               :distribution in Korean. However, they are not in free variation. In Korean, a resumptive pronoun tends
line=226 fonts=F2-10.9 iscore=0.21 bbox=72.0,403.02,443.93,413.93               :to occur in a deeply embedding structure as in (17), but not in a simple TC as in (18).

