line=243 fonts=F2-6.0,F2-9.0 iscore=0.06 bbox=84.66,113.82,525.46,123.58                                                        :   ^{3}Georgopoulos (1991) argues that resumptive pronouns are variables by pointing out that they are subject to the same
line=244 fonts=F2-9.0 iscore=0.22 bbox=72.0,103.86,525.64,112.83                                                                :recoverability requirements as traces. She provides various syntactic evidence for the variable analysis, working mainly on
line=245 fonts=F2-9.0 iscore=0.06 bbox=72.0,93.9,102.51,102.87                                                                  :Palauan.
line=246 fonts=F1-9.0,F2-6.0,F2-9.0 iscore=0.00 bbox=84.66,82.98,525.58,92.8                                                    :   ^{4}In relative or topic constructions, the long distance reflexive caki ‘self’ can appear in the position of the trace as well
line=247 fonts=F2-9.0 iscore=0.14 bbox=72.0,73.02,525.57,81.99                                                                  :as resumptive pronouns. However, the distribution of the reflexive is more restricted because its antecedent should normally
line=248 fonts=F1-9.0,F2-9.0 iscore=0.22 bbox=72.0,63.06,525.53,72.03                                                           :be a subject. In tough constructions, a reflexive caki ‘self’ does not seem to occur in the position of a gap. However, when
line=249 fonts=F2-9.0 iscore=0.30 bbox=72.0,53.1,525.57,62.07                                                                   :we consider unbounded dependency  in Korean, the factors determining the distribution of gaps, a resumptive pronoun and a
line=250 fonts=F2-9.0 iscore=0.11 bbox=72.0,43.14,368.92,52.11                                                                  :reflexive should be clearly explained. We will leave this issues for the future study.

