line=302 fonts=F2-10.9 bbox=72.0,520.5,525.71,531.41                                         :In this section, we present a lexical analysis of the formation of Korean TCs and discuss how to represent
line=303 fonts=F2-10.9 iscore=0.05 bbox=72.0,506.94,525.68,517.85                            :relevant syntactic and semantic information. Long distance connectivity of TCs can be encoded in the
line=304 fonts=F1-10.9,F2-10.9 iscore=0.18 bbox=72.0,493.38,525.66,504.29                    :lexical entries of tough predicates. As mentioned before, there are two kinds of TCs, ones taking ki-ey
line=305 fonts=F1-10.9,F2-10.9 iscore=0.29 bbox=72.0,479.82,525.66,490.73                    :phrases and ones taking ki-ka phrases. Lexical entries of tough predicates that require ki-ey and ki-ka
line=306 fonts=F1-10.9,F2-10.9 iscore=0.29 bbox=72.0,466.32,525.53,477.23                    :phrases are distinct in their VALENCE features. We provide a lexical entry of swipta ‘easy’ having a
line=307 fonts=F1-10.9,F2-10.9 iscore=0.12 bbox=72.0,452.76,173.86,463.67                    :ki-ey phrase as follows.
