line=391 fonts=F1-10.9,F2-10.9 bbox=82.92,512.52,525.59,523.43                                               :  Even  though a relativizer nun and an adverbializer key change the function of sentences to work as
line=392 fonts=F2-10.9 iscore=0.16 bbox=72.0,499.02,525.63,509.93                                            :modifiers in (28), we do not need to assume that they change the syntactic categories of the whole phrase.
line=393 fonts=F1-10.9,F2-10.9 iscore=0.21 bbox=72.0,485.46,399.62,496.37                                    :In English, that clauses can replace NPs withouth having the status of NPs.
line=394 fonts=F2-10.9 iscore=0.06 bbox=82.92,471.9,525.52,482.81                                            :  A  notable point is that the information of a complementizer is visible by the main predicate and the
line=395 fonts=F2-10.9 iscore=0.28 bbox=72.0,458.34,525.64,469.25                                            :complementizer markes the whole phrase as one consitituent. In order to capture this fact, we use the
line=396 fonts=F2-10.9 iscore=0.24 bbox=72.0,444.78,525.52,455.69                                            :MARKING     (MARK)   feature as a HEAD feature that is introduced by the lexical rule that attaches a
line=397 fonts=F2-10.9 iscore=0.20 bbox=72.0,431.22,525.52,442.13                                            :nominalizing suffix to the stem of a prediate in (26). In addition, we argue that the CASE feature is not
line=398 fonts=F1-10.9,F2-10.9 iscore=0.20 bbox=72.0,417.72,525.74,428.63                                    :a HEAD   feature of noun in Korean. It can be supported by the fact that a case marker morphologically
